{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban state schools from making Religious Studies a mandatory GCSE subject",
        "additional_details": "GCSE results can have a massive impact on a student\u2019s study opportunities after year 11, and forcing them to take exams on religions that they may not believe in could mean that their grades may suffer, limiting future study options. I think that students should focus on subjects that align with their interests, not be forced into Religious Studies.",
        "background": "We call on the government to ensure that Religious Studies is not a compulsory GCSE subject in state schools. We believe that students should have the freedom to choose subjects that align with their interests and beliefs.",
